body:
@davisp @jiangphcn With 2.2.0 down to just 4 open issues, and already with PSE in there, let's release that first.

Please hold merging these purge PRs until the 2.2.0 release is cut.

I anticipate that in the next 2 weeks or less.

>  indicates how catched up view is to a database

@eiri  Thanks. I missed this obvious part 😄  . 
So at the moment the only problem left with the implementation advised here [in this PR](https://github.com/apache/couchdb-chttpd/pull/90#discussion_r43617014) is that (as you said) different nodes can have different `update_seq` and we don't have atomic broadcast in the couch cluster, right?

@newtewt That may no longer be the correct place for local.ini, and I have no experience with the OSX packaging contributed by @janl , so I can't help.

What I can say is that the settings linked in the documentation work on Linux and Windows, so I am thinking this is something specific to the OSX binary.

We don't support this binary within the Apache project.  You'll want to report the bug over at https://github.com/janl/build-couchdb-mac , sorry.
